samophis.lavalink.client.entities

Interface LavaHttpManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LavaHttpManagerImpl

    public interface LavaHttpManager
    This class is the manager which allows LavaClient to send requests to get information from a track for use in both the client and the server.
    Since:
    0.1

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Fetches the LavaClient associated with this manager.

    • Method Detail

      • getClient

        @Nonnull
LavaClient getClient()
        Fetches the LavaClient associated with this manager.
        Returns:
        The LavaClient attached to this manager.

      • resolveTracks

        void resolveTracks(@Nonnull
                   java.lang.String identifier,
                   @Nonnull
                   java.util.function.Consumer<AudioWrapper> callback)
        Sends a request to the AudioNode with the least load on it to resolve track(s) based on the provided identifier.
        Parameters:
        identifier - The not-null identifier from which the tracks are derived.
        callback - The not-null callback to use, accepting a not-null AudioWrapper object.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If the provided identifier or callback are null.

      • shutdown

        void shutdown()
        Shuts down the internal HTTP Client used to make requests in the first place.

        This is called by the LavaClient.shutdown() method too.

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If this manager has already been shut-down.
